post_text: Este es un recordatorio para completar el Censo de 2020. El Censo 2020 de los Estados Unidos es cómo el gobierno cuenta nuestra población. Determina cómo se gastarán miles de millones de dólares de dinero federal en servicios importantes, incluyendo las escuelas. Ocurre solo una vez cada diez años, por lo que ahora es nuestra oportunidad de asegurarnos de ser contados. El censo tiene solo nueve preguntas simples y toma solo unos minutos para completar. Puede completar el censo en línea en www.2020census.gov o puede completar el formulario en papel que recibió por correo. La ley exige completar el censo y su información personal no se compartirá con ninguna otra agencia gubernamental. Si no completa el censo, un trabajador del censo visitará su hogar para revisar si lo ha completado. Así que complete el censo hoy para asegurarse de que el Condado de Ventura obtenga los recursos que merece. Nuevamente, el sitio web del censo es www.2020census.gov. Gracias.

post_text: This is a reminder to complete the 2020 Census. The 2020 United States Census is how the government counts our population. It determines how billions of dollars in federal money will be spent on important services, including schools. It happens only once every ten years, so now is our chance to be sure we’re counted. The census has just nine simple questions and takes only a few minutes to finish. You can complete the census online at www.2020census.gov or by filling out the paper form that you may have received in the mail. Completing the census is required by law and your personal information won’t be shared with any other government agency. If you don’t complete the census, a census worker will be visiting your home to follow up. So complete the census today to be sure that Ventura County gets the resources it deserves. Again, the census website is www.2020census.gov. Thank you.

Ocean View School District is sharing this important update from Ventura County Public Health.

Ventura County continues to see an increase in COVID-19 cases, and we want to ensure that all residents have the information they need to prevent COVID-19 infection. It’s important to remember that gatherings with anyone other than members of your household are prohibited. Here are some basic things that you can do to reduce your risk and the risk for others of infection.

1) Wash your hands with soap and water for at least 20 seconds.
2) Don’t touch your nose, mouth or eyes and teach your children to do the same.
3) Maintain 6 ft. distance from others when leaving your house and in public areas.
4) Use face coverings when leaving your home and going out into
public areas. This is State mandated.

If you think you have COVID-19 or have been exposed to someone with it, get tested for free. There are various locations throughout the county.

Please go to the website www.venturacountyrecovers.org for all COVID-19 related information for Ventura County.

Ocean View School District
iPad Distribution Schedule

District staff will distribute one iPad to each family with students in grades TK-5 that do not have access to technology at home, on Friday, March 20, 2020, at Ocean View Junior High, 4300 Olds Road. The distribution will follow this schedule:

Laguna Vista Families: 8:30am-10:00am
Mar Vista Families: 10:30am-12:00pm
Tierra Vista Families: 12:30pm-2:00pm
Make-ups: 2:30pm-3:30pm

The distribution will be a drive thru/walk thru format for parents/guardians. We urge you to have only one parent/guardian per household to pick up the iPad. Please be prepared to show a form of ID.

A separate line will also be available for those who are unable to drive through at their designated time.

Please observe instructions of social distancing:
As you arrive, please ensure to remain 6 feet away from any other person. If you are sick, please stay home

IMPORTANTE: Actualization sobre el cierre del Distrito Escolar Ocean View
Dada la información actual, las Escuelas de Ocean View permanecerán cerradas al menos hasta el viernes 1 de mayo de 2020. El personal está planificando en caso de que se necesite extender tal cierre. Nos comunicaremos con usted a medida que haya más información disponible. Nuestro personal está trabajando en planes para el aprendizaje a distancia para nuestros estudiantes durante este cierre prolongado. Como parte de este plan, planeamos distribuir una tableta iPad a cada familia con estudiantes en los grados TK-5, el viernes 20 de marzo de 2020. Más detalles sobre la distribución estarán disponibles mañana, jueves 19 de marzo de 2020, a través de la página web del distrito sitio web y nuestras otras plataformas de comunicación.

IMPORTANT: Update on Ocean View School District closure
Based on current information, Ocean View Schools will remain closed at least through Friday, May 1, 2020, and staff are planning ahead in case further closure is needed. We will communicate with you as more information is available. Our staff is working on enhanced plans for distance learning for our students during this extended closure. As part of this plan, we plan to distribute one iPad to each family with students in grades TK-5, on Friday, March 20, 2020. More details about distribution will be available tomorrow, Thursday, March 19, 2020, through the district website and other communication systems. Have a good evening.

post_text: Recent national events, the current political climate, and the unprecedented acts of Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE), have increased the uncertainty, anxiety and fear for many in our schools and community. The Ocean View School District Governing Board redesignated all district facilities as safe havens or sanctuary sites regardless of immigration status. As Superintendent, I am proud to share Resolution No. 19-09, ensuring that our District is a safe place for all students and families!

The Ocean View School District Transportation Department is hiring School Bus Drivers. Base pay is $18.77 to $22.93, per hour, for a minimum of 3-4 hours per day. Three (3) positions are open.

Extra hours are available for School Sponsored Trips and cleaning buses throughout the year. Each driver receives an additional ten (10) hours of pay for training during the year.

Drivers may be eligible for additional positions at school sites depending on the hours and schedule.

Our Driver Trainer can help you with the required certifications.

As evening closes on the sixth day of the county fires, be reassured that NBVC is continuing to monitor the status of the #WoolseyFire which experienced a flare up earlier this afternoon. NBVC Fed Fire works closely with Ventura County Fire and CAL Fire, receiving updates regularly.
The fires are currently being held at a safe distance from NBVC Point Mugu.
Should conditions shift, NBVC residents will be notified well in advance.
Your safety and security are our top priority.
We have personnel monitoring conditions throughout the night.
Rest easy NBVC.

post_text: La primera prioridad del distrito escolar Ocean View es el cuidado y la seguridad de los estudiantes. Nuestra prioridad es atender a nuestros estudiantes y a la comunidad mientras mantenemos la seguridad de todos. Hemos vigilado cuidadosamente la calidad del aire durante el día, y continuaremos haciéndolo cada hora. En este momento, confiamos que nuestras escuelas están seguras y con nuestro plan, los estudiantes pueden asistir a sus clases normalmente. Continuaremos vigilando la calidad del aire y proveeremos información cuando haya cambios en las circunstancias. Esta notificación será actualizada y mañana enviaremos un mensaje telefónico a las 6 am confirmando nuestras intenciones de mantener las escuelas abiertas y/o proveer cualquier otra información adicional.

shared_text:
Congresswoman Julia Brownley
May 11, 2018 at 8:05 AM ·

This week, I had the honor of speaking at the “Recognizing Inspirational School Employees” (RISE) Award ceremony to recognize my constituent, Maria Tapia, who works as the librarian at Ocean View Junior High School in Oxnard. Whether it is encouraging kids to read for pleasure, aiding students with their work, fostering collaboration on group projects, or making sure that students who feel out of place have a space where they can feel comfortable, Maria goes above and beyond to make Ocean View Junior High a better place for our young people. Maria, congratulations on the well-deserved honor, and thank you for all of your tireless, amazing work for the students at Ocean View Junior High School! In Congress, I am a cosponsor of the Recognizing Achievement in Classified School Employees Act, which would require the Department of Education to recognize the exemplary service of classified school employees, like Maria, who go the extra mile in their service to students.

post_text:
On Tuesday, March 13, 2018, the Governing Board of the Ocean View School District unanimously passed a resolution advocating for reasonable gun control, requesting sufficient funding to support our students’ physical, mental and emotional health and development, and opposing arming teachers or staff members. The letter and resolution was sent to state and federal officials. #ENOUGH

El martes 13 de marzo de 2018, la Mesa Directiva del Distrito Escolar Ocean View aprobó por unanimidad una resolución que aboga por un control de armas razonable, solicita los fondos suficientes para apoyar el desarrollo y la salud física, mental y emocional de nuestros estudiantes, y se opone a armar a los maestros o a personal escolar. La carta y la resolución se enviaron a los funcionarios estatales y federales.
text:
On Tuesday, March 13, 2018, the Governing Board of the Ocean View School District unanimously passed a resolution advocating for reasonable gun control, requesting sufficient funding to support our students’ physical, mental and emotional health and development, and opposing arming teachers or staff members. The letter and resolution was sent to state and federal officials. #ENOUGH

El martes 13 de marzo de 2018, la Mesa Directiva del Distrito Escolar Ocean View aprobó por unanimidad una resolución que aboga por un control de armas razonable, solicita los fondos suficientes para apoyar el desarrollo y la salud física, mental y emocional de nuestros estudiantes, y se opone a armar a los maestros o a personal escolar. La carta y la resolución se enviaron a los funcionarios estatales y federales.

Ocean View School District is working on a transition to solar power… as part of the process, our district offices will be closed January 4th due to a necessary power outage. Phones and e-mail will be functional again when offices reopen on January 5th. Thank you for your patience.

El Distrito Escolar de Ocean View está haciendo una transición hacia la energía solar. Como parte del proceso, nuestras oficinas del distrito estarán cerradas el 4 de enero, debido a un corte de electricidad. Las líneas telefónicas y correo electrónico estarán en función nuevamente cuando la oficina abra nuevamente el 5 de enero. Gracias por su paciencia.

UPDATE 12/18/17: We have been monitoring air quality forecasts and communicating regularly with other agencies. Finally, it appears that air quality will be within the good range the remainder of the week. Ocean View will reopen all schools starting tomorrow, Tuesday, December 19, 2017. We look forward to welcoming you all back prior to the holidays. Thank you once again for your patience, cooperation and flexibility during this situation.

NOTICIAS 12/18/17: Hemos seguido monitoreando el pronóstico del tiempo y manteniendo comunicación con otras agencias. Por fin, la calidad de aire estará en buen indice mañana y por el resto de la semana. Las clases reanudarán en el Distrito Escolar de Ocean View mañana martes 19 de diciembre. Esperamos con anticipación verlos de regreso antes de los días festivos. Gracias nuevamente por su paciencia, cooperación y flexibilidad durante esta situación.

post_text:
UPDATE, as of Sunday 12/17/17
After monitoring changing weather patterns and air quality, and with consultation with other agencies, we anticipate unhealthy air for sensitive individuals tomorrow morning and again in the afternoon. For this reason, Ocean View will remain closed on Monday, December 18th. We remain anxious for lost instructional time for our students, and District administrators will regroup tomorrow to determine whether to reopen on Tuesday. Thank you again for your cooperation and flexibility during this time.

NOTICIAS , domingo 12/17/17
Al monitorear las condiciones variables tanto como la calidad de aire, y en consulta con otras agencias, anticipamos aire no saludable para individuos sensibles durante la mañana y en la tarde. Por este motivo, nuestras escuelas permanecerán cerradas el día lunes, 18 de diciembre. Seguimos ansiosos por el tiempo perdido para nuestros alumnos. Mañana, los administradores determinarán si las clases reanudarán el martes. Gracias nuevamente por su cooperación

For Your Information

FAILING GRADE GIVEN TO PROPOSED TRUMP EDUCATION BUDGET: State Superintendent of Public Instruction Tom Torlakson has urged Congress to reject President Trump’s federal education budget proposal, which includes deep cuts to teacher training, after school programs, mental health services, advanced coursework, and many other important programs.

Para Su Información
Calificación deficiente otorgada a la propuesta del presupuesto de educación de Trump: El Superintendente Estatal de la Instrucción Pública, Tom Torlakson, ha urgido al Congreso a que rechaze la propuesta del presupuesto de educación del Presidente Trump, el cual incluye cortes profundos al entrenamiento de maestros, programas después de escuela, servicios de salud mental, cursado avanzado, y muchos programas importantes.

post_text:
Mr. Robert "Bob" Allen passed away last week. He served as Superintendent from 1974 to 1992, retiring after 18 years of service as Superintendent in Ocean View. He was only the second Superintendent in Ocean View history. Our sincere condolences to his family and friends.

El Sr. Robert "Bob" Allen se murió la semana pasada. Él sirvió como Superintendente desde 1974 hasta 1992, se retiró después de 18 años de servicio como Superintendente del distrito escolar Ocean View. Fue el segundo Superintendente en la historia de este distrito. Nuestras sinceras condolencias a su familia y amigos.
